item.title: Coronavirus Explosion Forecast for One Indian State
item.description: As the pandemic’s U.S. death toll passed 112,000 and reported cases topped 1.9 million, Paris’s public transport system faces a revenue slump and the Indian state of Delhi forecasts 550,000 cases by the end of next month.

item.title: Deaths Prompt Questions About Covid-19 Safety in Mexico Factories
item.description: Workers and their families at factories in Mexico along the U.S. border say companies are resisting closing plants to protect employees amid the coronavirus pandemic.

item.title: China and India Pull Back From Himalayan Standoff
item.description: The two nuclear powers have started to withdraw forces from their disputed border, a source of tension since their 1962 war.

item.title: Chinese Sports Power Couple Issues Rare Rebuke of Communist Party
item.description: Retired soccer star Hao Haidong and his wife, former badminton world champion Ye Zhaoying are speaking out to support a fugitive Chinese businessman’s campaign to topple Beijing’s leadership.

item.title: After 34 Years, a Political Assassination in Europe Remains Shrouded in Mystery
item.description: The investigation into the murder of Swedish Prime Minister Olof Palme is now closed, but the mystery surrounding one of postwar Europe’s most prominent political killings will likely endure given that the only suspect is dead.

item.title: U.S. Sends Aircraft Carriers as China Makes Waves in the Pacific
item.description: The deployments of the USS Ronald Reagan and USS Nimitz boost the U.S. naval presence as China’s military steps up its activity in the region.
